Scalability concerns
Matchmaking
Single global Redis queue — no separation by bot, platform, gender/age filters, or region; hot queue under load.
FIFO list + LPUSH/RPOP — fair but no priority or preference matching.
Lua script reduces races; still no distributed lock around ChatService::startChat if two workers match the same user via DB race (mitigated partly by active-room checks, not by DB unique constraint).
Messaging
No async delivery yet — synchronous connector calls from webhook will timeout under load.
No idempotency keys for webhook retries (Telegram/Bale resend updates).
No pagination/archival strategy for messages table growth.
Wallet
wallets.balance updates without documented locking — race conditions on concurrent deposit/withdraw.
No immutable ledger pattern (transactions should be append-only with balance derived or locked updates).
Redis / queues
Matchmaking uses Redis; default app queue is database — mixed infrastructure increases ops complexity.
No Horizon → no visibility into queue depth, failed jobs, or scaling workers.
Filament / admin
Listing bot tokens and unbounded message/room tables will not scale in admin UI without filters, pagination defaults, and policy scopes.
Multi-tenancy (bots)
Multiple bots share one match queue — users on different bots could be matched together unless queue key includes bot_id.
Recommended implementation order
Phase 0 — Foundation (unblock everything)
Goal: Migrations run; enums work; services autoload; admin can log in.

Add migration: users.status (offline, searching, chatting), auto-uuid on create.
Fix User model: $fillable, casts (uuid, dates), remove or split admin auth from platform User.
Create Admin model + migration (email/password) or use Filament’s dedicated admin approach; point Filament guard to it.
Fix HasOptions namespace + add label() to enums (or use Filament ->options() from enum cases directly).
Add namespaces to PlatformResolver, WalletService, ReferralService.
Fix UserFactory, add factories for Bot, UserAccount, ChatRoom, Wallet.
Fix DatabaseSeeder for local dev.
Add indexes: chat_rooms(status), chat_rooms(user1_id, status), chat_rooms(user2_id, status); unique(referred_user_id) on referrals.
Pest tests: ChatService, MatchService (Redis fake or integration).
Exit criteria: php artisan migrate:fresh --seed works; Filament login works; enum selects do not error.

Phase 1 — Platform wiring (Bale MVP)
Goal: Bot can receive and send messages.

Implement PlatformResolver (+ bind in AppServiceProvider if needed).
Implement BaleConnector::sendMessage (HTTP, timeouts, retries).
config/services.php entries for Bale base URL / defaults.
routes/api.php + BaleWebhookController (thin).
Actions:
ResolveOrCreateUserAccount (bot + platform user id → User + UserAccount + Wallet)
HandleBaleUpdate (dispatch by command type)
Register webhook route; middleware: throttle, bot token verification.
Exit criteria: Manual webhook POST creates user account; bot can send a test message.

Phase 2 — Chat & match orchestration
Goal: Two Bale users can match and exchange messages.

Action StartSearching → putInQueue + findPartner; notify both on match (connector).
Action CancelSearch → removeFromQueue.
Action SendChatMessage → ChatService::sendMessage + queue DeliverOutboundMessageJob.
Job delivers to partner’s primary (or active) UserAccount for same bot/platform.
Action EndChat → ChatService::endChat + removeFromQueue + notify partner.
Optional: scope matchmaking Redis keys by bot_id.
Integration tests: two users match, message relay, end chat.
Exit criteria: End-to-end anonymous match + text chat on Bale.

Phase 3 — Wallet & referral
Goal: Monetization / growth mechanics per architecture.

Implement WalletService with DB::transaction + lockForUpdate on wallet row.
Link Transaction to wallet_id (migration) if ledger clarity is required.
Implement ReferralService::rewardReferrer.
Hook referral creation into user onboarding / start command.
Filament: WalletResource, TransactionResource (read-only create from app only).
Phase 4 — Cross-platform linking
Goal: One User, multiple user_accounts.

LinkCodeService — create/expired codes.
Action LinkPlatformAccount — validate code, attach account, merge rules.
Filament LinkCodeResource (support/debug).
Phase 5 — Media & profile
Goal: Non-text messages + profile completion.

S3-compatible disk config; upload Action from webhook file payloads.
Extend ChatService::sendMessage / job for IMAGE, VOICE, etc.
Profile completion flow in bot commands.
Phase 6 — Admin & operations
Remaining Filament resources + relation managers (Bot → UserAccount).
Mask tokens; use KeyValue / JSON editor for settings.
Install Horizon; switch queues to Redis; DeliverOutboundMessageJob on dedicated queue.
Logging, failed-job alerts, health checks.
Phase 7 — Hardening & expansion
Telegram / Rubika (when in scope).
Policies (Spatie) for Filament roles.
Load testing matchmaking queue; tune Redis memory and TTL for stale queue members.
Message table partitioning / archival policy.
